@node Folder configuration
@section Folder configuration

@vindex mu4e-extras-inbox-folder
@vindex mu4e-extras-daily-folder
@vindex mu4e-extras-newsletters-folder
The user option @code{mu4e-extras-inbox-folder} specifies the maildir path
for the main inbox folder.  It is used by @code{mu4e-extras-set-shortcuts} to
configure maildir shortcuts (@ref{Setup helpers}).  The default value is an
empty string; you must set this to match your maildir layout (e.g.,
@samp{"/gmail/Inbox"}).

The user option @code{mu4e-extras-daily-folder} specifies the maildir path
for a ``daily'' folder, also used by @code{mu4e-extras-set-shortcuts}.  The
default value is an empty string.

The user option @code{mu4e-extras-newsletters-folder} specifies the maildir
path for a newsletters folder.  The default value is an empty string.
This option is available for use in custom configurations but is not
referenced by any default function in the package.

@node Reply behavior
@section Reply behavior

@vindex mu4e-extras-wide-reply
The user option @code{mu4e-extras-wide-reply} controls the default behavior
when replying to messages with multiple recipients.  It accepts three
values:

@itemize
@item
@code{prompt} (the default): ask the user whether to reply to all.
@item
@code{t}: always reply to all recipients.
@item
@code{nil}: always reply only to the sender.
@end itemize

This option is consulted by @code{mu4e-extras-compose-reply}
(@ref{Composing messages}).  When the original message has only a single
recipient (excluding the sender), the option has no effect and a normal
reply is always used.

